article.description:
Steve Burtt scored 27 points and Kiril
Wachsmann added 16 to lead Iona to a 93-75 victory over Buffalo on
Saturday.
article.headline: Burtt, Iona cruise past Buffalo
article.story:
NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Steve Burtt scored 27 points and Kiril Wachsmann added 16 to lead Iona to a 93-75 victory over Buffalo on Saturday.
Running Down

Utah State Northwestern St. 66-63
Creighton Fresno State 67-62
Ricky Soliver had 14 points, and Marvin McCullough and Kenny Jackson scored 10 apiece for the Gaels (20-5), who won their fourth in a row. Yassin Idbihi scored 13 points and Calvin Cage and Roderick Middleton added nine each for the Bulls (16-10), who have lost six of their last seven games. Burtt, who had five 3-pointers, scored 15 points in the first half to help Iona take a 45-34 halftime lead. Wachsmann scored the first five points of the second half to push the Gaels' lead to 50-34. Parnell Smith's basket cut the margin to 54-40 with 16:34 left, but Buffalo never got any closer the rest of the way. The Gaels led by as much as 85-53 after Burtt converted two free throws with 6:46 to go.
